  <front>
   <head>INVOCATION TO CUPID. TO FREDERICK REYNOLDS, ESQ.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">DECK'D with rays of purple light,</l>
     <l n="2" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Hither, Cupid, wing thy flight;</l>
     <l n="3" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Through the pure unclouded sky</l>
     <l n="4" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Let thy shafts unnumber'd fly.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Bid the warblers of the grove</l>
     <l n="6" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Bow before the shrine of Love;</l>
     <l n="7" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">And with thy resistless dart</l>
     <l n="8" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Pierce, O pierce each youthful heart.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Hark, how round thy hallow'd shrine,</l>
     <l n="10" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Sweetly chaunt the tuneful Nine;</l>
     <l n="11" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">O'er the green enamel'd plains</l>
     <l n="12" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Pouring all their magic strains.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Phoebus now with fervid rays</l>
     <l n="14" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Lights thy altar's holy blaze;</l>
     <l n="15" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">And, touching soft his magic lyre,</l>
     <l n="16" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Joins the sweet Aonian choir.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
